review_blob: It upsets me that this stuff claims to be Australian. Its Canadian! Brewed by Molson! For a spell it was brewed by AB in Los Angeles, CA. In any event, it hasnt been from "down under" for a long-time now. I wrote the FTC and they told me that they would "look into my claim" of false advertising. I swear this beer used to be better when it was actually brewed and bottled in the nation continent. Now, its just an average lager.

What do you want for a beer that sells for $3.99 a sixer? I find it "just as good" as Coors, Bud, Miller, etc. I dont like the fact that it comes from St. Louis, Missouri, now, instead of "the glass lined tanks of old Latrobe."
A good "go-to" beer. It never disappoints and is nice on a cold or hot day. Most always a pretty good deal to boot!

Simply put, this is not a good IPA. Its not even a good beer. Ive been on a tight budget of late and thought I would treat myself $6.99 six-pac. I shouldve stuck with my $3.99 Rolling Rock. It was that bad.
